Code Explanation:
Header and Footer: The header includes an image and the report title. The footer displays the current page number.
Data Table: The Table() function receives headers and data to build a table in the PDF. Column widths are defined in an array, and the table layout is formatted using cells (Cell()).
Image in Header: Image() adds an image to the top of the page, adjusting its position and size.
PDF Output: Output('I', 'sales_report.pdf') opens the PDF in the browser. To force the download, change 'I' to 'D'.